The FDA said last week after Vioxx was withdrawn that the problems were unique to that drug.
Heavily advertised as an arthritis drug, Vioxx was pulled from the market last week after its maker said a study showed it doubled the risk of heart attack and stroke.
Merck &amp; Co. removed Vioxx from use Thursday after new study results showed increased risk of heart attacks and stroke in people who used it for longer than 18 mon
Merck took the drastic step of pulling Vioxx because its research showed it caused increased risk of heart attack.
But Northwestern University rheumatologist Thomas Schnitzer argued for ditching Vioxx entirely because Merck's scientists could not explain why the drug started causing heart attacks after 18 months.
